  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel <strong>half </strong>your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and slice<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into thin rings</p><p>Add the<strong> onion rings</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and set aside to pickle – this is your <strong>quick-pickled onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1616673189156-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1616673189156-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1616673189156-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1616673189156-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1616673189156-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 30 min or until crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616673193560-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616673193560-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616673193560-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616673193560-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616673193560-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chips are in the oven, peel and grate the <strong>remaining red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>grated onion</strong>,<strong> </strong>your<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>lean beef mince</strong> to a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix thoroughly until fully combined, then shape into 1<strong> </strong>lean beef burger patty per person</p><p>Add the<strong> lean beef burger patty[ies] </strong>to a separate, lightly oiled baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616673198839-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616673198839-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616673198839-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616673198839-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616673198839-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the lean beef burger patties are cooking, chop your<strong> parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>mint</strong> finely, discard the stalks</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>red chilli[es] </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1616673258736-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1616673258736-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1616673258736-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1616673258736-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1616673258736-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>and <strong>mint</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a small splash of<strong> cold water</strong></p><p>Grind the mix to a paste, then add your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped red chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> of your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> from the quick-pickled onion – this is your <strong>chimichurri mayo</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s] </strong>in half</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616673263157-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616673263157-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616673263157-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616673263157-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616673263157-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) (or griddle if you have one), over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>brioche halves</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 3 min or until toasted and charred, then set them aside until serving</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Do this is in batches!</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1616673267966-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1616673267966-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1616673267966-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1616673267966-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1616673267966-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lean beef burger patty is cooked, remove the tray[s] from the oven and top them with the<strong> grated cheese</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 3-4 min or until the cheese has melted – this is your <strong>cheesy lean beef burger patty[ies]</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, separate your <strong>lettuce </strong>into leaves, then wash them thoroughly and pat them dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1616673273125-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1616673273125-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1616673273125-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1616673273125-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1616673273125-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To build, top each <strong>toasted brioche base</strong> with a few <strong>lettuce</strong> <strong>leaves</strong>, a <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>lean</strong> <strong>beef</strong> <strong>burger</strong> <strong>patty</strong>, some <strong>quick-pickled</strong> <strong>onion</strong>, a dollop of <strong>chimichurri</strong> <strong>mayo</strong> and the <strong>toasted brioche lid </strong>– this is your <strong>cheesy lean beef burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>chips</strong>, any <strong>remaining lettuce leaves </strong>and <strong>remaining chimichurri mayo</strong> to the side, then top the lettuce leaves<strong> </strong>with any <strong>remaining quick-pickled</strong> <strong>onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
